UNICEF Report – Youth HIV Knowledge Around the World

Author

Saniya Mansuri

Published

April 27, 2025

Introduction

Young people are at the heart of the global fight against HIV. Ensuring that adolescents and youth have comprehensive, correct knowledge about HIV prevention is critical to ending the epidemic. This report explores global trends in youth HIV knowledge, highlighting progress made and the gaps that still remain.

Comprehensive HIV education empowers young people to make safe choices. Higher levels of knowledge are linked to lower infection rates.

Code 


# Install required packages (hide output)

# Import libraries
import polars as pl
import pandas as pd
from plotnine import *
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload the indicator file (hide output)
from google.colab import files
_ = files.upload()

# Load the indicator dataset
indicator = pl.read_csv(
    "unicef_indicator_1.csv",
    schema_overrides={"time_period": pl.Utf8}
)
Code 
# Lowercase indicators
indicator = indicator.with_columns(
    pl.col("indicator").str.to_lowercase()
)

# Fix time_period safely
indicator = indicator.with_columns(
    pl.col("time_period").str.slice(0, 4).alias("time_period")
)
indicator = indicator.with_columns(
    pl.col("time_period").cast(pl.Int32)
)

# Now filter for HIV knowledge
data_hiv = (indicator
    .filter(pl.col("indicator").str.contains("hiv"))
    .filter(pl.col("time_period") >= 2000)
    .filter(pl.col("obs_value").is_not_null())
    .filter(pl.col("obs_value") > 0)
)

Latest HIV knowledge globally

Code 
shape_world = gpd.read_file("https://public.opendatasoft.com/api/explore/v2.1/catalog/datasets/world-administrative-boundaries/exports/shp")

hiv_latest = (data_hiv
    .sort(["country", "time_period"], descending=[False, True])
    .group_by("country")
    .agg(pl.col("obs_value").first().alias("latest_obs_value"))
)

map_data = shape_world.merge(hiv_latest.to_pandas(), left_on="name", right_on="country", how="left")

map_data['latest_obs_value'] = pd.to_numeric(map_data['latest_obs_value'], errors='coerce').fillna(0)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 10))
shape_world.boundary.plot(ax=ax, linewidth=1, color="black")
map_data.plot(column="latest_obs_value",
              cmap="YlGnBu",
              linewidth=0.8,
              ax=ax,
              edgecolor='0.8',
              legend=True,
              legend_kwds={'label': "% Youth with Comprehensive HIV Knowledge"})
plt.title("Global Youth HIV Knowledge (Latest Available Year)", fontsize=20)
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()

Top 10 countries by highest HIV knowledge

Code 
top10_hiv = hiv_latest.sort("latest_obs_value", descending=True).head(10)

(ggplot(top10_hiv.to_pandas())
 + aes(x='reorder(country, latest_obs_value)', y='latest_obs_value', fill='country')
 + geom_col()
 + coord_flip()
 + labs(title="Top 10 Countries by Youth HIV Knowledge",
        x="Country",
        y="% Youth with Comprehensive HIV Knowledge")
 + theme_bw()
)

HIV knowledge over time

Code 
(ggplot(data_hiv.to_pandas())
 + aes(x='time_period', y='obs_value')
 + geom_point(alpha=0.6)
 + labs(title="Youth HIV Knowledge Over Time",
        x="Year",
        y="% Youth with Comprehensive HIV Knowledge")
 + theme_light()
)

Global average HIV knowledge over time

Code 
hiv_global = (data_hiv
    .group_by("time_period")
    .agg(pl.col("obs_value").mean().alias("global_avg"))
)

(ggplot(hiv_global.to_pandas())
 + aes(x='time_period', y='global_avg')
 + geom_line()
 + geom_point()
 + labs(title="Global Average Youth HIV Knowledge Over Time",
        x="Year",
        y="Global Average %")
 + theme_minimal()
)

Using UNICEF data, we analyzed the percentage of young people with comprehensive, correct knowledge of HIV prevention. Our analysis includes a world map showcasing the latest coverage rates, a bar chart highlighting top-performing countries, a scatter plot illustrating patterns over time, and a time-series chart showing global average trends from 2000 to 2020.

Some countries have achieved high youth HIV knowledge rates, nearing 80–90%. In many regions, especially in parts of Sub-Saharan Africa and South Asia, gaps in awareness still exist. Globally, there has been steady improvement over the last two decades — but progress is uneven across regions.

While the world has made significant strides in educating young people about HIV, continued investment in education and awareness programs is vital. Closing the knowledge gap will not only protect today’s youth, but will build healthier, more resilient communities for the future.
